args: Ho there, Cleo! What are you up to?
I didn't think I was being quite so stealthy.\n...What's this, then? Are you painting?
Is this a picture of a group of fiends?!\nHow horrid and frightening they look!
...It's a portrait of everyone in the castle.
...OoooOOOOooo! Yes, of cooourse!\nI see it now! It's soooo beautifâ€”
Stop. I'm quite aware of my lack of skill.
*sigh* Let me ask you something, Celliera.\nYou're rather...driven. Can you think of a\nway I might improve my talents?
Actually, now that you mention it,\nI may have an idea.
When drawing a person, being conscious\nof their musculature will allow you to\ndepict them with greater accuracy.
Is that so? ...Huh. I learned something.
Learned something? Leeeearning...\nA-HA! This is where I come in!
I will teach you all about muscles!
Precisely. If you become more familiar\nwith human musculature, your artwork\nwill soar to new heights!
Ah, I see. And since your profession\ninvolves training people, you're something\nof an expert in the subject.
Well, if you're willing to teach me,\nI would love to learn.
I'm on the case! Henceforth, please refer\nto me as ï¼‚master!ï¼‚
With my own body as a model, I will teach\nyou all there is to know about muscles!
This here is the biceps brachii, which you\ncan flex to see in greater detail. And here\non the calf we have the triceps surae.
You can deepen your comprehension even\nfurther by not just looking, but touching.\n...Go on! See how they feel!
Goodness! It's like they're made of iron.\n
And yet they're so slender. I'd always\nthought that lots of muscle training would\ncause them to become quite thick.
Such slender grace is a result of my body\ntype and training regimen.
I had no idea muscles could be such a\ncomplex topic.

Moving on! The teres major is below the
armpit, and then you have the rectus
abdominis, which runs along the anterior
of the abdomen. ...Go on! Touch!
Er, touch your armpit and abdomen?
It's fine. This is for your art, after all.\nNow come get your hands-on training!
Very well, Master. And apologies for being\nso up close and personal...
Hee... Eee hee... Eeeeee hee heee!
Hmm. I think I have a better idea of which\nmuscle is which now.
Excellent! Then let us continue touching\neach and every other muscle.
...And with that, you've now handled\nevery single one of my muscles.
Now for the next step! As I mentioned,\nmusculature differs based on the person.
By which I mean we'll be touching\nsomeone ELSE'S muscles now! Onward!
Looks like it's about time for me to start\nmy training...
AUGH! C-Celliera, what are you doing?!
This is for art! For CLEO'S art!\nNow sit there and behave!
Cleo! Come touch {player_name}\nto your heart's content!
Umm...I think this might be going a bit\noverboard.
DO NOT HESITATE! Steel yourself!\nDo it for art!
C-Cleo? Why are you holding your hands\nlike that...?
Aaaaah! What the heck are... Aaaah ha!\nY-you're tickling mâ€”AAAAH HA HA HA!
Did they do it to you, too, Elisanne?
Same here. Cleo came at me screamin'\nabout how it was for art or somesuch.
Why would they need to go around\ntickling people for the sake of her art?
So she might learn about human\nmusculature and make use of it in her\nportraiture! ...Obviously.
And thanks to your cooperation,\nCleo now knows about muscles on a\nmost intimate basis.
Really? Huh. Well, I was shocked at the\ntime, but so long as we were able to help,\nthat's what matters most.
And just a little while ago, I posed for her\nin order to test the results of her studies.
Come, Cleo! Show off your artwork to all!
What is it? I'd like to see what kind of\nportrait you produced.
I'm eager to see how much you've\nimproved as well! What with my\nposing, I didn't even catch a glance.
You hidin' it behind your back there?\n*yoink*
This is amazing! Your portrayal of Celliera\nis so good, it seems like she might just\nwalk right out of the piece! But, um...
Why are her right and left legs different\nsizes?
My head is bizarrely huge. It's three times\nlarger than my body!
Looks like a new breed of fiend if ya\nask me.
I can draw each part of the body now,\nbut I didn't do a good job with the whole\n...balance thing.
What should I do now, Master?
Now that things have come to this,\nlet me borrow some white cloth, Cleo.
Huh? White cloth? I can do that, but, er...\nWhat are you going to do with it?
I'm going to wave it with all my strength!
I surrender! I SURRENDER!\nYou are completely hopeless!
